From Stan Armstrong Subject Re Prodigal Son The parable of the Prodigal Son is not about who is and who isn't an immoral It is about grace and the love of Most people would agree with that concerning the younger The elder son is simply a negative example of the some He thinks that he must earn his father's love that he has earned it that he is entitled to His father tells him that he is on the wrong He has always been loved for the same reason his brother has always been he is his father's We are too performance oriented to consistently get the We are willing to be saved by grace but once we are Christians we want to go back to earning and Are you so foolish After beginning with the Spirit are you now trying to attain your goal by human effort Gal NIV Stan Religious Studies Dept Saint Mary's University Halifax A att clyde watmath water dalcs armstrng